Privacy Policy – Math Games for Kids: Counting
Effective Date: March 9, 2026
Last Updated: March 9, 2026

1. Introduction
Welcome to Math Games for Kids: Counting ("the App"). We are committed to protecting the privacy of all users, especially children. This Privacy Policy explains what information is collected, how it is used, and your rights regarding that information.

By using the App, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

2. Information We Collect
Information We Do NOT Collect
We do not collect names, email addresses, phone numbers, or any personally identifiable information (PII).
We do not require account registration or login.
We do not collect location data.
We do not access your camera, microphone, or contacts.
We do not share any data with third parties for marketing purposes.
Information Stored Locally on Your Device
All app data — including player profiles, scores, achievements, and settings — is stored locally on your device only. This data never leaves your device and is not transmitted to any server.

3. Advertising (Google AdMob)
The App displays advertisements provided by Google AdMob. AdMob may collect certain non-personal, aggregated data to display ads, including:

Device type and operating system version
General location (country/region, not precise GPS)
Ad interaction data (impressions, clicks)
This data is collected by Google under their own privacy policy. We have configured AdMob to comply with children's privacy regulations (COPPA/GDPR-K). You can review Google's privacy policy at: https://policies.google.com/privacy

To opt out of personalized advertising on your device, go to:
Settings → Google → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalization

4. Children's Privacy (COPPA Compliance)
This App is designed for children. We comply fully with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and similar regulations worldwide.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
We do not allow in-app purchases.
We do not include social features, chat, or user-generated content sharing.
Advertising shown in the App is configured for child-directed treatment as required by Google AdMob policies.
Parents and guardians may contact us at any time to request deletion of any locally stored data by simply uninstalling the App.

5. Permissions Used
The App requests the following device permissions:

Permission	Purpose
INTERNET	Required for displaying AdMob advertisements
ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE	Checks network availability before loading ads
VIBRATE	Provides haptic feedback during gameplay
FOREGROUND_SERVICE	Keeps background music running while app is in use
No other permissions are requested or used.

6. Data Security
Since all user data is stored locally on your device and no personal information is transmitted to external servers, your data is as secure as your device itself. We recommend keeping your device protected with a screen lock.

7. Data Retention & Deletion
All app data (profiles, scores, settings) is stored locally. To delete all data, simply uninstall the App from your device. Uninstalling removes all associated data permanently.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected with a new "Last Updated" date. Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

